Mexican Stocks: Geo, Homex, Urbi Decline; Grupo Bimbo Advances

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-03-04T22:48:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/mexican-stocks-geo-homex-urbi-decline-grupo-bimbo-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.6 percent to 36,900.84.  Homebuilders dropped on concern credit expansion may slow
as a surge in oil prices threatens global economic growth.  Corp. GEO SAB (GEOB MM), Mexico’s second-largest
homebuilder, dropped 2.8 percent to 32.60 pesos.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX* MM), Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, retreated 1.6 percent to 53.03 pesos.  Urbi Desarrollos Urbanos SAB (URBI* MM), Mexico’s third-
largest homebuilder, slumped 2.3 percent to 26.11 pesos.  Grupo Bimbo SAB (BIMBOA MM), the world’s largest bread
maker, climbed 1.9 percent to 97.32 pesos, leading gains on the
benchmark index. Morgan Stanley raised its recommendation on the
company to “overweight” from “equalweight.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  